[BLOWS WHISTLE]

17:38.013 --> 17:38.970
-HEY.

17:39.101 --> 17:40.276
-GET ON!

17:41.234 --> 17:42.452
WHAT ARE YOU GUYS, DEAF?

17:42.583 --> 17:44.541
-NO, THEY'RE NOT
DEAF. THEY'RE WIMPS.

17:44.672 --> 17:47.283
-YEAH, LOTS OF ATTITUDE,
BUT NO GANAS, HUH?

17:47.414 --> 17:49.285
-YOU KNOW, MAYBE
WE OUGHT TO FORGET

17:49.416 --> 17:51.157
THIS BOAT RIDE AND SEND
THEM TO BEAUTY SCHOOL.

17:53.333 --> 17:54.116
-HEY, HEY.

17:54.247 --> 17:55.857
-ALRIGHT, LET'S MOVE.

17:55.987 --> 18:00.122
-EASY, EASY, EASY,
EASY, COME ON.

18:03.691 --> 18:04.822
COME ON, EASY.

18:04.953 --> 18:05.693
-EVERYBODY ON.
-WELCOME TO THE,

18:05.823 --> 18:07.347
THE WATER PROGRAM, BOYS.

18:07.912 --> 18:12.091
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

19:54.628 --> 19:57.283
-OKAY, MOVE A LITTLE
BIT TO YOUR LEFT.

19:57.413 --> 19:58.893
GREAT.

19:59.023 --> 20:00.634
OKAY, LOOK THIS WAY.

20:00.764 --> 20:02.375
GREAT.

20:02.505 --> 20:03.941
GREAT.

20:04.072 --> 20:05.029
[CAMERA CLICKING]

20:05.160 --> 20:06.117
OKAY, A LITTLE BIT TO THE RIGHT.

20:06.248 --> 20:07.467
OKAY, AND LOOK TOWARDS ME.

20:08.119 --> 20:09.643
BEAUTIFUL. GREAT.

20:10.470 --> 20:11.906
OKAY, YOU LOOK GREAT.

20:12.036 --> 20:13.473
-ALL RIGHT, HERE WE GO.

20:14.561 --> 20:15.736
COME ON.

20:15.866 --> 20:17.868
BATHROOMS ARE STRAIGHT AHEAD.

20:19.479 --> 20:21.437
I DON'T THINK HE'S
GOING TO MAKE IT.

20:22.351 --> 20:24.048
GOOD TIME, HUH?

20:26.529 --> 20:28.749
YOU KNOW, THERE'S NO
CRIME IN ADMITTING,

20:28.879 --> 20:31.055
YOU'RE HAVING A GOOD TIME
EVERY ONCE IN A WHILE.

20:33.057 --> 20:34.450
HEY LOOK, MAN, MAYBE, UH,

20:34.581 --> 20:36.713
MAYBE, SOMETIME,
I COULD HELP OUT?

20:36.844 --> 20:38.628
-NO ONE HELPS
MEMO BUT MEMO, ESE.

20:38.759 --> 20:40.587
-I THINK YOU'RE WRONG.

20:41.457 --> 20:42.980
-A GUY CAN GET HURT
TALKING LIKE THAT.

20:43.111 --> 20:45.679
-RIGHT NOW, YOU'RE THE
ONE THAT'S GETTING HURT.

20:45.809 --> 20:46.941
-MEMO!

20:47.681 --> 20:49.160
GET YOUR STUFF. YOU'RE
OUT OF HERE, ORALE.

20:49.683 --> 20:51.119
-I DON'T THINK SO.

20:51.859 --> 20:53.556
-HEY, NOBODY CARES
WHAT YOU THINK.

20:53.687 --> 20:56.516
-HEY MAN, IT'S THIS
PROGRAM OR IT'S JAIL.

20:56.646 --> 20:58.648
-YEAH WELL, JAIL'S NOT
SO BAD. I'VE DONE MY TIME.

20:58.779 --> 21:00.041
-SO HAVE I.

21:00.955 --> 21:02.304
I GUARANTEE YOU,

21:03.174 --> 21:05.655
HE'S GONNA LEARN A
LOT BETTER THINGS HERE
THAN HE EVER WILL IN THERE.

21:05.786 --> 21:06.656
-BETTER FOR WHAT?

21:07.440 --> 21:08.789
NOT BETTER FOR MY WORLD.

21:09.442 --> 21:10.530
-MAYBE HE WANTS TO STAY.

21:12.488 --> 21:13.315
-DO YOU WANT TO STAY?

21:14.229 --> 21:15.186
-NO, MAN.

21:15.317 --> 21:16.840
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

21:26.546 --> 21:30.419
[MOTORCYCLE REVVING]

21:35.032 --> 21:37.731
-WELL, MIKE, CALL GARNER.

21:37.861 --> 21:39.472
HEY, GUYS, COME
ON, LET'S GO, HUH?

21:39.602 --> 21:40.995
WE GOT A LOT OF
THINGS TO DO YET,

21:41.125 --> 21:42.823
UNLESS YOU GUYS WANT
TO BE PUT AWAY TOO.

21:42.953 --> 21:44.781
-ANYTHING WOULD BE BETTER
THAN GOING BACK ON THAT BOAT.

21:44.912 --> 21:46.783
-CHECK OUT THE BLOND CHICK.

21:47.523 --> 21:48.916
-DO WE REALLY HAVE
TO GO DOWN THERE?

21:49.046 --> 21:51.266
I THOUGHT YOU SAID WE'D
BE OUT OF HERE BY THREE.

22:04.845 --> 22:06.803
JOHN D. CORT?

22:07.674 --> 22:09.937
-GUILTY AS CHARGED. HEY.

22:10.067 --> 22:11.025
-HEY.

22:11.155 --> 22:12.200
-MM.

22:12.331 --> 22:13.593
-MM. I HEARD YOU
WERE IN AFRICA.

22:13.723 --> 22:15.682
-WELL, I WAS.

22:15.812 --> 22:17.988
WHAT DO YOU SAY WE
GET TOGETHER TONIGHT
AND TALK ABOUT BIG GAME?

22:18.119 --> 22:19.642
-MMM.

22:19.773 --> 22:21.252
I LIKE IT.

22:22.166 --> 22:26.649
[MELLOW MUSIC]

22:40.271 --> 22:41.403
-HI.
-HI.

22:42.535 --> 22:44.885
UM, I KNOW IT'S LATE.

22:45.015 --> 22:46.234
-EDDIE, COOL IT.

22:47.409 --> 22:48.758
-OKAY.

22:48.889 --> 22:50.151
-LOOK, I DIDN'T COME
HERE TO GET ON YOU

22:50.281 --> 22:51.718
ABOUT STAYING OUT LATE.

22:51.848 --> 22:54.242
I JUST WANTED TO MAKE
SURE YOU GOT HOME SAFE.

22:55.548 --> 22:57.376
-AND, UM, HOW DO
YOU KNOW I WASN'T

22:57.506 --> 22:58.986
GOING TO BE OUT ALL
NIGHT WITH CORT?

22:59.116 --> 23:00.422
-BECAUSE CORT CALLED ME.

23:00.553 --> 23:02.555
HE'S BEEN CALLING
ME EVERY HALF HOUR.

23:02.685 --> 23:05.384
WHY WERE YOU THE ONE TO
TAKE THOSE KIDS HOME ALONE?

23:07.516 --> 23:09.300
-I'VE BEEN OUT
LOOKING FOR MEMO.

23:13.000 --> 23:14.436
I KNOW HE HAD A GOOD
TIME ON THE SCARAB.

23:15.524 --> 23:16.612
HE WON'T ADMIT IT.

23:17.613 --> 23:19.746
HE WANTS TO BE A PART
OF THIS PROGRAM, SHAUNI.

23:19.876 --> 23:21.312
HE'S HAVING A GREAT TIME,
BUT FOR SOME REASON,

23:21.443 --> 23:23.793
HE WON'T OPEN UP.

23:23.924 --> 23:26.405
-YOU MEAN, LIKE YOU AT
THE Y POOL IN PHILLY?

23:28.624 --> 23:30.583
-YEAH, LIKE ME AT
THE Y POOL IN PHILLY.

23:31.235 --> 23:32.236
-AND THEN THERE WAS THAT GUY.

23:34.630 --> 23:35.544
-DENNY CURREN.

23:37.328 --> 23:40.810
I HATED THAT GUY.
HE WAS SO HARD ON ME.

23:44.074 --> 23:45.685
GREATEST MAN I'VE EVER KNOWN.

23:47.164 --> 23:49.079
ANYTHING I AM TODAY,
I AM BECAUSE OF HIM.

23:49.689 --> 23:51.038
-WELL NOW IT'S
YOUR TURN, EDDIE.

23:51.168 --> 23:52.431
DON'T LET THIS KID
GET AWAY FROM YOU.

23:52.561 --> 23:54.128
YOU'VE GOT TO MAKE
THIS WORK FOR HIM.

23:56.652 --> 23:58.437
YOU GOT TO MAKE IT WORK FOR YOU.

24:06.662 --> 24:10.449
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

24:24.419 --> 24:26.900
[CAR HORN HONKING]

24:30.077 --> 24:31.818
-[SPEAKING SPANISH]

24:31.948 --> 24:34.298
-I SUPPOSE YOU STILL
HAVEN'T SEEN MEMO.

24:34.429 --> 24:35.909
-MAN, ARE YOU CRAZY?

24:36.039 --> 24:37.171
I TOLD YOU FOUR HOURS AGO
THAT I AIN'T SEEN HIM,

24:37.824 --> 24:39.739
AND I SURE AS HELL
DIDN'T SEE HIM IN MY BED.

24:40.827 --> 24:42.393
-SO HOW DO WE FIND HIM?

24:42.524 --> 24:43.960
[LAUGHING]

24:45.135 --> 24:46.310
-WE DON'T.

24:46.441 --> 24:48.269
[LAUGHING]

24:48.399 --> 24:49.662
-WE DO.

24:50.271 --> 24:51.751
-YOU ARE CRAZY, HUH?

24:51.881 --> 24:53.883
NO ONE MESSES WITH MEMO'S PADRE.

24:54.014 --> 24:56.190
HE SITS ON YOU, YOU
REAL DEAD, HOMES.

24:56.320 --> 24:58.061
-YEAH, WE'LL SEE.

25:01.412 --> 25:03.545
-I GOT DIBS ON THE
COWBOY'S WATCH, EH?

25:03.676 --> 25:05.373
[LAUGHING]

25:11.597 --> 25:16.384
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

25:44.499 --> 25:46.632
-IF THE OLD MAN'S
HERE, BUY ME SOME TIME.

25:51.462 --> 25:52.768
[KNOCKING]

25:58.208 --> 25:59.645
-I'M BUSY.

25:59.775 --> 26:01.690
-HEY, UH, WE JUST WANT TO TALK.

26:01.821 --> 26:03.300
-YOU KNOW WHAT? GET
OFF MY PROPERTY, MAN.

26:03.431 --> 26:04.345
GET OFF MY PROPERTY.

26:04.998 --> 26:06.260
-OR WHAT? YOU'RE
GONNA CALL THE LAW?

26:06.390 --> 26:08.392
-HEY, IN THIS
BARRIO, I AM THE LAW.

26:11.134 --> 26:14.398
[FIGHTING NOISE]

26:15.704 --> 26:16.879
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE, MAN?

26:17.010 --> 26:19.665
[FIGHTING, GRUNTING]

26:19.795 --> 26:21.014
-HEY, COME ON.

26:21.884 --> 26:23.930
-TRYING TO GIVE YOU
SOME OTHER OPTIONS.

26:24.060 --> 26:25.496
-I DON'T NEED OPTIONS, ESE.

26:25.627 --> 26:27.194
I GOT EVERYTHING I NEED.

26:28.325 --> 26:30.110
-WELL, YOU HAVE A FATHER,
THAT'S ONE UP ON ME.

26:30.240 --> 26:32.634
[CRASHING]

26:32.765 --> 26:34.593
-I HOPE I'M BUYING
YOU ENOUGH TIME.

26:37.770 --> 26:38.901
-I DON'T KNOW.

26:39.772 --> 26:41.904
WHEN I THINK ABOUT IT,
WHEN PUSH CAME TO SHOVE

26:42.035 --> 26:44.428
THE ONLY THING EVER HOLDING
ME BACK WERE MY OWN FEARS.

26:45.081 --> 26:46.517
-NOW, COME ON!

26:46.648 --> 26:49.956
[FIGHTING, GRUNTING]

26:52.132 --> 26:53.220
[GRUNTING]

26:53.350 --> 26:54.874
-CORT, IT'S ALL RIGHT, MAN.

26:55.004 --> 26:56.397
COME ON, COME ON, THAT'S ENOUGH.

26:57.180 --> 26:58.399
ALL RIGHT.

27:00.314 --> 27:01.532
-THE MAN SAYS YOU'RE AFRAID.

27:01.663 --> 27:02.533
-WHAT, OF HIM?

27:02.664 --> 27:04.100
-NO.

27:04.231 --> 27:05.493
AFRAID OF WHAT MEMO
MIGHT LEARN OUT THERE.

27:06.668 --> 27:08.670
-WHAT? HOW TO BE A
CUTE LITTLE SURFER, HUH?

27:08.801 --> 27:10.890
HOW TO GET A NICE TAN?

27:11.020 --> 27:12.500
WELL, YOU SEE ANY
WAVES AROUND HERE?

27:12.631 --> 27:14.850
-NO MAN, THERE WERE NO
WAVES WHERE I GREW UP EITHER.

27:14.981 --> 27:16.678
I DIDN'T EVEN SEE THE
OCEAN UNTIL I WAS 19.

27:16.809 --> 27:19.072
ALL ANYONE EVER OFFERED
ME WAS A 10-BY-20 POOL

27:19.202 --> 27:21.552
WITH CHIPPED TILES,
STINKING OF CHLORINE.

27:22.466 --> 27:25.774
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?
IT WAS ANOTHER LIFE, MAN.

27:26.340 --> 27:27.428
IT WAS ANOTHER LIFE
OTHER THAN THE ONE

27:27.558 --> 27:28.951
THAT I THOUGHT I WAS STUCK IN.

27:30.431 --> 27:32.259
-YEAH, SO MEMO
GETS OUT THERE, HUH,

27:32.389 --> 27:34.043
GETS A TASTE OF SOMETHING.

27:34.174 --> 27:35.610
WHAT HAPPENS WHEN
HE WANTS MORE, ESE?

27:35.741 --> 27:38.134
HE GETS DOORS
SLAMMED IN HIS FACE.

27:38.265 --> 27:40.833
YEAH, BECAUSE OF WHO HE IS,
BECAUSE OF WHERE HE'S FROM.

27:40.963 --> 27:42.486
-IT DOESN'T HAVE
TO BE THAT WAY.

27:42.617 --> 27:44.140
-DON'T TELL ME.

27:44.271 --> 27:46.708
I KNOW AND I KNOW
WHERE HE BELONGS.

27:46.839 --> 27:48.667
AROUND HERE, MEMO'S
BIG TIME, ESE.

27:49.624 --> 27:51.582
HE GETS RESPETO,
YOU UNDERSTAND?

27:51.713 --> 27:53.497
EVERYBODY KNOWS
WHO HE IS, HOMES.

27:53.628 --> 27:55.282
-SO WHAT?

27:55.412 --> 27:58.720
SO WHAT, IN TIME, HE HAS
TATTOOS ALL OVER HIS ARMS,

27:58.851 --> 28:01.375
KNIFE SCARS ON HIS CHEST OR
WORSE YET HE ENDS UP DEAD.

28:01.505 --> 28:02.376
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT, ESE?

28:04.726 --> 28:05.684
GO INSIDE, MEMO.

28:09.122 --> 28:11.298
YOU KNOW WHAT? YOU GUYS
GET YOUR BUTTS OUT OF HERE.

28:12.560 --> 28:13.387
GET OUT OF HERE NOW!

28:13.517 --> 28:15.258
AND YOU TELL THEM COPS,

28:16.564 --> 28:18.218
THEY WANT TO COME TAKE HIM,

28:18.348 --> 28:20.133
THEY'LL NEVER MAKE IT
THROUGH MY FRONT YARD.

28:24.572 --> 28:26.574
-WELL, THAT WAS INTERESTING.

28:26.705 --> 28:28.315
-YOU EVER GET SO
MAD, YOU WANT TO PUT
YOUR FIST THROUGH A WALL?

28:28.445 --> 28:30.491
-ACTUALLY, I FEEL
LIKE I JUST DID.

28:30.621 --> 28:31.579
-HEY, LISTEN. YOU WERE GREAT.

28:31.710 --> 28:33.450
-NO, MAN, YOU WERE GREAT.

28:33.581 --> 28:35.061
IF IT HAD BEEN ME YOU
WERE RECRUITING IN THERE,

28:35.191 --> 28:36.410
I WOULD HAVE JOINED UP.

28:39.935 --> 28:40.849
[CLOSES CAR DOOR]

28:45.201 --> 28:46.768
-WHAT ARE WE WAITING FOR?

28:46.899 --> 28:48.727
THERE'S THIS WHOLE NEW
WORLD AT THE BEACH, RIGHT?

28:56.212 --> 28:57.605
-HEY.
-HEY.

28:57.736 --> 28:59.302
-HEY, COME ON, NOW.

28:59.433 --> 29:01.348
GO CHANGED IN THE LOCKER ROOM.
LET'S GO, COME ON.

29:01.478 --> 29:03.132
-HEY, YOU LOOKING FINE.

29:05.439 --> 29:07.615
-COME ON, COME ON.
HUSTLE UP. SURF'S UP.

29:12.925 --> 29:16.015
-DIO! THESE THINGS MADE
FOR HUMANS? [LAUGHS]

29:16.145 --> 29:18.104
-HEY, NOBODY SAID
THAT GOOD CLEAN FUN

29:18.234 --> 29:19.105
WAS GOING TO BE EASY.

29:19.235 --> 29:20.628
-COME ON. HERE WE GO.

29:20.759 --> 29:21.847
